        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: show in-flight feedback on manual refresh",
        "body": "## Problem\r\n\r\nClicking **Refresh** while the menu is open gives no immediate feedback. The currently-visible provider card keeps showing its old `Updated …` subtitle, and the persistent **Refresh** row looks idle, until the network round-trip (0.5–5s) completes. The \"Refreshing…\" state only became visible after switching to a *different* card.\r\n\r\nRoot cause: the open root menu is intentionally **not** rebuilt during NSMenu tracking (the deferred-rebuild policy that avoids mid-tracking layout jumps / freezes). The \"Refreshing…\" state already existed in the model, but nothing pushed it onto the *already-open* views — so it never rendered until a rebuild happened on the next menu open.\r\n\r\nBecause there's no feedback, users click Refresh repeatedly, and each click fires another cookie-based backend request.\r\n\r\n## Fix\r\n\r\nSurface the in-flight state **in place**, without rebuilding the menu during tracking:\r\n\r\n- **Provider card subtitle** — a narrowly-scoped `MenuCardRefreshMonitor` bridge over the observable `UsageStore` is injected via a SwiftUI `@Entry` environment value. The header view reads `isRefreshingIndicatorVisible(for:)` and swaps the subtitle to `Refreshing…` in place. Existing `.error` subtitles remain authoritative, including errors derived outside `UsageStore.error`, so the multi-line error layout and copy affordance are never replaced.\n- **Persistent Refresh row** — the leading `arrow.clockwise` icon is swapped for a spinner occupying the **same fixed 18pt slot** (icon faded via `alphaValue`, not `isHidden`, so the `NSStackView` slot never collapses and the title doesn't shift). The spinner is forced on at click for instant feedback, then synced to `store.isRefreshing` from the store observation (covering both success and failure paths).\r\n\r\nBoth updates are in-place AppKit/SwiftUI mutations on existing views — no `NSMenu` rebuild — so they're safe during menu tracking and don't reintroduce the layout-jump regressions the deferral policy guards against.\r\n\r\n## Tests\r\n\r\n3 new tests in `StatusMenuPersistentRefreshTests` (7/7 in the suite pass):\r\n- spinner toggling keeps fixed row metrics (height/intrinsic/fitting unchanged)\r\n- persistent refresh rows reflect store refresh state in place\r\n- the monitor mirrors the store's refreshing-indicator gate\r\n\r\n`swift build` clean; full suite green.\n\nMaintainer follow-up on rebased head:\n- preserve existing error subtitles during live refresh\n- switch the spinner to a high-contrast appearance while the row is highlighted\n- add changelog credit\n- `swift test --filter StatusMenuPersistentRefreshTests` (7/7)\n- `make check`\n- Codex autoreview: clean\n\r\n## Proof\r\n\r\n<img width=\"310\" height=\"818\" alt=\"Ghostty 2026-06-12 13 31 35\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/da18b073-c29e-4b6d-abac-45541592fdec\" />\r\n",
        "branch": "feat/refresh-in-flight-feedback",
